msgid "An Offer You Can't Refuse"
msgstr "不容拒绝的报价"

msgid "Interlude I: An Offer You Can't Refuse"
msgstr "幕间故事I：不容拒绝的报价"

msgid "\"What you have recovered is no mere curio. It was bought at great expense from a dealer in Egypt, who inherited it from a relative who bought it in Peking, you know how it goes,\" Randall smirks as you admire the ancient artifact. It is a vaguely humanoid figure, sitting in a stooped position, with a heavy, octopoid head and squid-like features. There is something malevolent in its expression, something unwholesome in the very way it was sculpted. You find it difficult to look away."
msgstr "“你找回来的东西可不仅仅是件珍宝。你懂的，这是花了大价钱从一个埃及商人那里买来的，而这个埃及人又是继承的亲戚从北京买的宝物……”看到你在欣赏这件古代的神器，兰道尔露出了坏笑。这雕像依稀有个人形，俯身坐着，长着个大大的章鱼脑袋，身上也像乌贼。这东西看着就不怀好意，雕刻的样式令你浑身不自在。你发现自己已经很难移开视线了。"

msgid ""
"\"This is a singular relic of prehistoric, dare I say, pre-human origins,\" Randall's voice breaks the spell. The rest of the eccentric antiquarian's story boggles the mind. He describes a record of some ancient cosmic struggle, and how he believes that all of earth is on the cusp of an apocalypse, much like the one that destroyed the statue's creator."
"In all of human history—in every separate mythology—there exists a story of a great flood. A cataclysm. There are legends of a great city-state: a bastion of knowledge and might, that sank beneath the waves. Humankind has named it many things. Atlantis. Mu. Lemuria. But its true name, a name that predates history, is <i><b>R’lyeh</b></i>."
"\"Through much painstaking research, and the assistance of a mad sailor named Gustaf, I have pinpointed the relative coordinates of the ancient city. A stretch of ocean in the South Pacific where many sailing vessels have shipwrecked or disappeared with no explanation. Which brings me to my offer. I need someone bold and resourceful to lead an expedition to the ancient city. Someone to bring back evidence of its ancient knowledge, study its secrets, record its wonders. I need that person to be you\" Randall says, looking to you, then to Ruby and Andy."
"\"Should you accept, I shall absolve you of any remaining debt and provide you enough money to retire comfortably. <i>Very</i> comfortably. And, of course, lend my assistance for your <i>other</i> concerns.\""
"Your mind wanders back to those other \"concerns.\""
msgstr ""
"“这件非凡的遗物来自史前，我敢说甚至在人类之前。”兰道尔终于开始讲到重点。这件神奇古物的传说，接下来的部分实在难以相信。他描述了一场史前的宇宙冲突，以及他相信地球上的一切即将面临一场灾变，正是这样的灾变在过去毁掉了雕像的创造者。"
"“在人类的全部历史中—在每个独自的神话体系里—都有一场大洪水的传说。一场大灾变。伟大城邦的传说一直存在：那里是承载无数知识和力量的宝库，却沉没在波涛之下。人类给它起过很多名字：亚特兰蒂斯、姆大陆、雷姆利亚（译者注：传说中存在于印度洋南端，后沉入海底的大陆）。但它真正的名字，在历史之前的名字，<i><b>拉莱耶</b></i>。"
"“我费尽千辛万苦，借由一个疯水手古斯塔夫的帮忙，已经定位出了这座远古城市的相对坐标。南太平洋上有一片海域，许多船只在那里遇难，或者莫名其妙地消失。这就是我之前说的报价：我需要勇敢机敏的人带头，去这座古代城市探险。得有人带回这些古代知识的证据，研究它的秘密，记录它的奇迹。我需要的人就是你。”兰道尔说着看向你，接着是露比和安迪。"
"“只要你接受，我就免除你所剩的债务，再给你一笔钱，足够你舒舒服服地退休。舒服得<i>难以置信</i>。当然了，我也会帮你处理<i>其他</i>事情。”"
"你的思绪回到了其他的<i>“事情”</i>上。"

msgid "You narrow your eyes at Randall. There's something he's not telling you. Some catch. There's always a catch with Tillinghast. Just as there's always one more job to be done. You ask him what it is and he sighs. \"I thought it was obvious, but this expedition is likely to be rather perilous. Which is why I thought to entrust it to you. You've proven yourself to be quite resourceful. And as I said, I intend to reward you handsomely\""
msgstr "你眯起眼晴盯着兰道尔。他没说全部。有所隐瞒，蒂林哈斯特向来有所隐瞒。就像永远都有新活要干一样。你问他在说什么，他则叹了口气：“我想这很明显，就是这趟探险可能非常危险。这也就是为什么我要交托给你。你证明了自己足够机警。而且正如我说的，我会好好的奖励你。”"

msgid "Refuse"
msgstr "拒绝"

msgid "Accept"
msgstr "接受"

msgid ""
"There has to be a catch. Tillinghast wouldn't offer such tempting bait otherwise. You're through with him. You shake your head no."
"\"Then get out,\" Tilhnghast says icily, pointing to the door. \"I have no further use for you. Rest assured, however, that if you speak a word of this to anyone, you will regret it.\" Without a word, you walk out of the shop, leaving behind whatever wonders—and dangers—Tillinghast had in store for you."
msgstr ""
"肯定有所隐瞒，不然蒂林哈斯特不会给出这么诱惑的报价。你受够他了。你摇了摇头说不。"
"“那么出去。”蒂林哈斯特指着门冷冰冰地说，“你对我没用了。不过，要是你跟别人说一个字，那你肯定是要后悔的。”你一言不发，走出了商店，把蒂林哈斯特准备的所有契机——不管是什么——还有危险，都抛在了身后。"

msgid ""
"Whatever his reasons for burying the lede, the offer is too tempting to refuse. Ruby and Andy nod along with you in agreement. Tillinghast's face breaks into a familiar smirk. \"How lovely. I'd hoped you would say yes. Truly, this is the opportunity of a lifetime. I assure you this will change <i>everything.</i>\"\n"
"After Andy negotiates for a comprehensive supply of film, and Ruby ups her commission,Tillinghast outlines the plan for the expedition. Tomorrow, a train will take you to San Francisco, where the <i>Cassandra</i> will sail you down to the provided coordinates in the South Pacific. There is an excited, almost childlike glee as the antiquarian outlines the details. \"I've sent supplies enough to last the entire expedition several months if needed. That said, be prepared for anything.\""
msgstr ""
"无论他为什么隐瞒，这份报价确实诱人，容不得拒绝。露比和安迪与你一起点头同意。蒂林哈斯特露出一个熟悉的坏笑：“多好啊。我就盼着你答应呢。说真的，这的确是一生难遇的机会。我保证这会改变一切。”"
"安迪的价码是要有大量的胶卷供应，露比则要求提高佣金。谈妥之后，蒂林哈斯特拿出了此次探险的纲要。你们明天将搭乘火车去旧金山，在那里登上卡珊德拉号，向南航行到南太平洋上的对应坐标。古董贩子在陈述细节的时候，露出了激动，甚至可以说是孩子气的欣喜：“我已经准备好了足够的补给，足以供应几个月的探险。也就是说，已经做好了万全的准备。”"

msgid "If an investigator has the [[Agency]], [[Detective]], or [[Criminal]] trait:"
msgstr "如果你的调查员有[[特工]]、[[侦探]]或[[罪犯]]特性："

msgid "Randall's operatic tale of the artifact's  acquisition seems needlessly contrived. You have every reason to believe the ancient statue was obtained through less than legitimate means. Sadly, this tells you nothing of the relic's true origins."
msgstr "兰道尔关于神器来源的叙述过于夸张，毫无必要，一看就是编的。你有十足的理由相信这件古代雕像来路并不合法。只是知道这点也没法帮你揭开其真实来源。"

msgid "In player order, each investigator chooses a different Task."
msgstr "按玩家顺序，每位调查员选择一个不同的任务，"

